Connectivity / Network Issues

JMeter Slave saturated → cannot process requests → Master Timeout

Pipeline execution time does not match the test SLA

RMI Timeouts due to default configuration

Machine Capability Assessment

| Resource | Lab Machine Specs                    | General JMeter Recommendation                  |
| -------- | ------------------------------------ | ---------------------------------------------- |
| CPU      | Intel i5-8500T – 6 cores / 6 threads | ✔️ Sufficient for medium-scale load generation |
| RAM      | 7.6 GB                               | ✔️ Good for GUI Master or low-load Slave       |
| Disk     | NVMe 218 GB                          | ✔️ Very good, fast and large enough            |
| Network  | Standard 1 GbE                       | ✔️ Suitable for distributed testing            |
| OS       | Ubuntu 24.04 LTS                     | ✔️ Fully compatible                            |

JMeter Performance Estimates

| Test Type            | Virtual Users     | Requests/sec      |
| -------------------- | ----------------- | ----------------- |
| Simple HTTP          | **1,500 – 3,000** | **200 – 800**     |
| HTTP with large JSON | **600 – 1,200**   | **80 – 300**      |
| WebSockets / gRPC    | **300 – 700**     | **<150**          |
| Selenium             | ❌ 5–20 browsers   | ❌ Not recommended |


Upgraded Slave (Memory Only)

| Resource | Upgraded Slave (RAM Only)            | General JMeter Recommendation                              |
